Turkey’s Basci Sees July Current Account Deficit Narrowing to $5 Billion

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-08-11T08:11:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/turkey-s-basci-sees-july-current-account-deficit-narrowing-to-5-billion.html
Turkish central bank Governor Erdem
Basci said he expects the country’s current-account deficit to
narrow to $5 billion in July and $27 billion in the second half
of the year. The gap in June was $7.5 billion.  Basci made the comments in an e-mailed response to
questions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steve Bryant in Ankara at 
 sbryant5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
